Standard Variable adapters for the NateChrony muzzle mounted Chronograph

Materials: Choose a material that has some flex/give, a very stiff/brittle material will crack due to the vibrations over time.
PLA/ABS is not recommended, we recommend a PETG based material.

Assembly Screws: Our adapters use A2 stainless countersunk M3x8mm thread forming/rolling trilobular thread, commercially known as plastite to assemble the adapters together.

Thumb Screws: Our adapters use an aluminium M6x20mm thumb screw, we recommend using the most coarse thread possible - either M6x1 or 1/4 20TPI are suitable.

All metal components should be non-oxidising, such as aluminium or stainless steel - A2/304
